messages.message:
A couple of things:
1. We seed the DB with the prebuilt roles in the post-install action `aihub-license`. I forgot to update the env var default value to true :sweat_smile: . I updated your `env-local-overrides.json` to this and then run the PIA
```{
  "base": {
    "enable_aihub_license_post_install_action": true,
    "enable_setup_prebuilt_roles": true
  }
}```
2. Then, I rollback back the migration 342 and re-apply the migration. We have to roll back because you already ran the migration so the DB refuse to apply the migration again. Your previous DB migration doesn't do anything because the prebuilt roles are not seeded.
